
<h1 aria-label="online" class="pb_title_kit_1">Opacity</h1>
<br>
<%= pb_rails("body", props: {
  text: "
  The word opaque is used for describing objects that are fully visible, i.e. with no transparency. 
  On a web page, a fully opaque element has an opacity value of 1 and a fully transparent element has an opacity value of 0. 
  By default, all elements have an opacity value of 1. From 0 to 1, the opacity property controls the transparency level of the element."
}) %>
